korean:
  title: 풍악
  author: 성석린
  language: kor
  text: |-
    일만 이천 봉은
    높고 낮음이 절로 다르네
    그대 보아라 해돋을 때에
    어느 곳이 가장 먼저 붉는가를
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0580&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Mount Fengwu
  author: Seong Seok-rin
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Twelve thousand peaks rise,
    Each claiming its own height.
    Watch when the sun breaks forth—
    Which summit blushes red first?
  footnotes:
    - Mount Fengwu (楓岳) refers to Diamond Mountains (Geumgangsan), a sacred peak in Korea celebrated in classical poetry for its majestic beauty and spiritual significance.
